cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper discusses the use of synthetic data to train neural networks for a recognition task, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of Bayesian modeling and approximate inference, which are relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of neural networks for the recognition of Captchas, which falls under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
